query: What is the total loan balance for customers who own at least one card?
sql_command: SELECT SUM(l.balance) FROM Loans l JOIN Customers c ON l.customer_id = c.customer_id JOIN Cards cd ON c.customer_id = cd.customer_id;

query: What is the number of deposits with interest rate less than 5% for customers with loans?
sql_command: SELECT COUNT(*) FROM Deposits d JOIN Customers c ON d.customer_id = c.customer_id JOIN Loans l ON c.customer_id = l.customer_id WHERE d.interest_rate < 5;

query: What is the total number of deposits for customers with more than one loan?
sql_command: SELECT COUNT(*) FROM Deposits d JOIN (SELECT customer_id FROM Loans GROUP BY customer_id HAVING COUNT(*) > 1) sub ON d.customer_id = sub.customer_id;

query: What is the number of customers from branch 4 with accounts, loans, and deposits?
sql_command: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT c.customer_id) FROM Customers c JOIN Accounts a ON c.customer_id = a.customer_id JOIN Loans l ON c.customer_id = l.customer_id JOIN Deposits d ON c.customer_id = d.customer_id WHERE c.branch_id = 4;

query: Count the number of accounts with balance above 1000 per branch.
sql_command: SELECT COUNT(*) FROM Accounts WHERE account_balance > 1000 AND customer_id IN (SELECT customer_id FROM Customers WHERE branch_id = 123);

query: Count the number of deposits with balance above average per branch.
sql_command: SELECT COUNT(*) FROM Deposits d JOIN Customers c ON d.customer_identifier = c.customer_id WHERE d.balance > (SELECT AVG(balance) FROM Deposits d2 JOIN Customers c2 ON d2.customer_identifier = c2.customer_id WHERE c2.branch_id = c.branch_id) AND c.branch_id = 123;

query: Count the number of transactions in the last 60 days per account.
sql_command: SELECT COUNT(*) FROM Transactions WHERE account_id = 123 AND transaction_date >= CURRENT_DATE - INTERVAL '60 days';

query: Count the number of transactions with amount above 500 in the last 6 months.
sql_command: SELECT COUNT(*) FROM Transactions WHERE transaction_amount > 500 AND transaction_date >= CURRENT_DATE - INTERVAL '6 months';

query: Count the number of accounts with more than 2000 in transactions.
sql_command: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT account_id) FROM Transactions GROUP BY account_id HAVING SUM(transaction_amount) > 2000;

query: How many customers belong to each branch in total?
sql_command: SELECT COUNT(*) FROM Customers c JOIN Branches b ON c.branch_id = b.branch_id;

query: What is the total balance of accounts in branches with more than 10 customers?
sql_command: SELECT SUM(a.account_balance) FROM Accounts a JOIN Customers c ON a.customer_id = c.customer_id JOIN Branches b ON c.branch_id = b.branch_id GROUP BY b.branch_id HAVING COUNT(c.customer_id) > 10;

query: What is the total account balance for each branch?
sql_command: SELECT SUM(a.account_balance) FROM Accounts a JOIN Customers c ON a.customer_id = c.customer_id JOIN Branches b ON c.branch_id = b.branch_id;

query: What is the total deposit balance per branch?
sql_command: SELECT SUM(d.balance) FROM Deposits d JOIN Customers c ON d.customer_id = c.customer_id JOIN Branches b ON c.branch_id = b.branch_id;

query: What is the total transaction amount per branch?
sql_command: SELECT SUM(t.transaction_amount) FROM Transactions t JOIN Accounts a ON t.account_id = a.account_id JOIN Customers c ON a.customer_id = c.customer_id JOIN Branches b ON c.branch_id = b.branch_id;

query: How many customers have both transactions and loans?
sql_command: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT c.customer_id) FROM Customers c JOIN Accounts a ON c.customer_id = a.customer_id JOIN Transactions t ON a.account_id = t.account_id JOIN Loans l ON c.customer_id = l.customer_id;

query: How many employees work in the bank?
sql_command: SELECT COUNT(*) FROM Employees;

query: How many customers are female?
sql_command: SELECT COUNT(*) FROM Customers WHERE gender = 'F';

query: How many customers are male?
sql_command: SELECT COUNT(*) FROM Customers WHERE gender = 'M';

query: How many employees have 'Manager' as their job title?
sql_command: SELECT COUNT(*) FROM Employees WHERE job_title = 'Manager';

query: How many employees work in the 'Finance' department?
sql_command: SELECT COUNT(*) FROM Employees WHERE department = 'Finance';

query: How many employees work in the 'IT' department?
sql_command: SELECT COUNT(*) FROM Employees WHERE department = 'IT';

query: How many employees have salaries greater than 50000?
sql_command: SELECT COUNT(*) FROM Employees WHERE salary > 50000;

query: How many employees have salaries less than 30000?
sql_command: SELECT COUNT(*) FROM Employees WHERE salary < 30000;

query: How many transactions are marked as 'Failed'?
sql_command: SELECT COUNT(*) FROM Transactions WHERE status = 'Failed';

query: How many transactions are marked as 'Successful'?
sql_command: SELECT COUNT(*) FROM Transactions WHERE status = 'Successful';

query: How many employees are supervisors?
sql_command: SELECT COUNT(*) FROM Employees WHERE job_title = 'Supervisor';
